article.headline: Lafayette 76, Army 73
article.story: WEST POINT, N.Y. (AP) -- Sean Knitter scored 21 points as Lafayette defeated Army 76-73 on Sunday. Matt Bell scored 30 points for Army (3-20, 1-10 Patriot League), and Cory Sinning added 20. The Black Knights trimmed Lafayette's lead to one point with 6.1 seconds remaining following three free throws by Bell, but then Knitter connected on two free throws with 5.5 seconds left to put the Leopards ahead 76-73. Lafayette (7-17, 2-9) led throughout the game and was ahead 65-53 with 6:46 to play when Army gradually worked its way back into the contest. Jamaal Douglas had 11 points and nine rebounds for Lafayette, which led 27-23 at the half. Marcus Harley had 13.
